# FlowSync Auth Service — Complete Codebase Flow

## Architecture Overview

The **authService** is a Spring Boot microservice running on port `8083` providing JWT-based authentication. It communicates with a **User Service** (port `8082`) during registration to create user profiles.

```mermaid
graph TB
    Client["Client / API Consumer"]
    
    subgraph AuthService["Auth Service :8083"]
        SF["Spring Security Filter Chain"]
        JF["JwtAuthenticationFilter"]
        AC["AuthController"]
        AS["AuthService"]
        JS["JwtService"]
        CUDS["CustomUserDetailsService"]
        REPO["AuthUserRepository"]
        GEH["GlobalExceptionHandler"]
    end
    
    DB[("PostgreSQL\nFlowSync-AuthService\n:5433")]
    US["User Service :8082"]

    Client -->|HTTP Request| SF
    SF --> JF
    JF --> AC
    AC --> AS
    AS --> JS
    AS --> REPO
    AS -->|POST /users/internal| US
    JF --> CUDS
    CUDS --> REPO
    REPO --> DB
    AC -.->|Exceptions| GEH
```

