## Detailed Request Flows

### 1. Registration Flow — `POST /api/auth/register`

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant SF as SecurityFilterChain
    participant JF as JwtAuthenticationFilter
    participant AC as AuthController
    participant AS as AuthService
    participant R as AuthUserRepository
    participant JS as JwtService
    participant US as User Service :8082
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    C->>SF: POST /api/auth/register<br/>{email, firstName, lastName, password, role}
    SF->>SF: CSRF check (should be disabled)
    SF->>JF: Pass to JWT filter
    JF->>JF: No "Authorization" header → skip auth
    JF->>AC: Forward to controller

    AC->>AS: register(RegisterRequest)
    AS->>R: existsByEmail(email)
    R->>DB: SELECT EXISTS
    DB-->>R: true/false

    alt Email already exists
        AS-->>AC: throw IllegalArgumentException
        AC-->>C: 400 Bad Request
    end

    AS->>AS: Generate UUID, encode password
    AS->>R: save(AuthUser)
    R->>DB: INSERT INTO auth_users
    DB-->>R: OK

    AS->>US: POST http://localhost:8082/users/internal<br/>{id, firstName, lastName, email}
    US-->>AS: UserResponse

    AS->>JS: generateToken(authUser)
    JS-->>AS: JWT token

    AS-->>AC: JwtResponse{token, userId, email, role}
    AC-->>C: 201 Created + JwtResponse
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `/api/auth/**` path is configured as `permitAll()` in `SecurityConfig`, so no authentication is required for this endpoint.

---

### 2. Login Flow — `POST /api/auth/login`

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant SF as SecurityFilterChain
    participant JF as JwtAuthenticationFilter
    participant AC as AuthController
    participant AS as AuthService
    participant AM as AuthenticationManager
    participant CUDS as CustomUserDetailsService
    participant R as AuthUserRepository
    participant JS as JwtService
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    C->>SF: POST /api/auth/login<br/>{email, password}
    SF->>JF: No Bearer token → skip
    JF->>AC: Forward

    AC->>AS: login(LoginRequest)
    AS->>AM: authenticate(email, password)
    AM->>CUDS: loadUserByUsername(email)
    CUDS->>R: findByEmail(email)
    R->>DB: SELECT * FROM auth_users
    DB-->>R: AuthUser

    alt Credentials Invalid
        AM-->>AS: throw BadCredentialsException
        AS-->>C: 401 Unauthorized
    end

    AM-->>AS: Authentication (principal = AuthUser)
    AS->>AS: authUser.updateLastLogin()
    AS->>R: save(authUser)
    R->>DB: UPDATE last_login
    DB-->>R: OK

    AS->>JS: generateToken(authUser)
    JS-->>AS: JWT token

    AS-->>AC: JwtResponse{token, userId, email, role}
    AC-->>C: 200 OK + JwtResponse
```

