### 5. Error Handling Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["Exception Thrown"] --> B{Exception Type?}
    
    B -->|JwtValidationException| C["401 Unauthorized<br/>JWT-specific error message"]
    B -->|BadCredentialsException| D["401 Unauthorized<br/>Invalid username or password"]
    B -->|AccessDeniedException| E["403 Forbidden<br/>Insufficient permissions"]
    B -->|MethodArgumentNotValidException| F["400 Bad Request<br/>Validation errors listed"]
    B -->|IllegalArgumentException| G["400 Bad Request<br/>e.g. Email already registered"]
    B -->|Any other Exception| H["500 Internal Server Error<br/>Unexpected error"]
```

All errors return a standardized `ErrorResponse` with: `status`, `error`, `message`, `details`, `path`.

