## JWT Token Structure

| Claim | Description | Example |
|-------|-------------|---------|
| `role` | User's role | `ROLE_USER` |
| `email` | User's email | `user@example.com` |
| `iat` | Issued at | Unix timestamp |
| `exp` | Expiration (24h default) | Unix timestamp |
| `jti` | Unique token ID | UUID |

> [!NOTE]
> The JWT does **not** set a `subject` claim. `extractUserId()` in `JwtService` calls `getSubject()` which will return `null`. The user is identified by the `email` claim instead.

