## ⚠️ Known Bug

> [!CAUTION]
> The `securityFilterChain()` method in [SecurityConfig.java](file:///Users/jai/Documents/FlowSync_microservices/authService/src/main/java/com/flowsync/authService/config/SecurityConfig.java#L40) is **missing the `@Bean` annotation**. This means Spring ignores the entire custom security configuration and uses default Spring Security — which has **CSRF enabled**, causing the 403 error on POST requests. Additionally, `.csrf()` and `.formLogin()` are each called twice (duplicates).

